The latest NTFS driver (2.1.5a) is now available for Linux kernel
2.4.23.

This updated release for Linux kernel 2.4.23 also includes a fix for a
problem encountered by at least two Windows XP users when accessing
certain fragmented files.

As always you can download a patch for the kernel from our website:

	http://linux-ntfs.sf.net/downloads.html

Or you can pull the changes from our bitkeeper repository:

	http://linux-ntfs.bkbits.net/ntfs-2.4

Note that the latest NTFS version (2.1.5) is also present in the current 2.6.0-test kernel and has been since 2.6.0-test9.

Happy NTFSing!  (-:

Best regards,

	Anton
